all_r3: (no endocard; remove valve)

After defining the endocardial population (and several very small groups of cells like Fbln5 and Hbb groups) in the previous step, analyze the rest of the cells with rPCA.

PC2 and PC3 scores show a continuum from valve-like (Corin+) to CV Plexus (Apln+)-like, connected by at least 2 distinct intermediate populations (Fbln2+, A2m+); however, there are too many intermediate populations for PCA to clearly separate them.

Use PC2.score and PC3.score to remove the Corin+/Fbln2- valve population and run rPCA on the rest of the cells so that heterogeneity in the rest of the continuum can be better revealed.

cells.allr3.valve = pc.scores[PC3.score < PC2.score + intercept, cell.name]
cells.allr3.rest = pc.scores[PC3.score >= PC2.score + intercept, cell.name]
# verify valve separation
with(pc.scores, plot(PC2.score, PC3.score, pch = 20)) +
  with(pc.scores[cell.name %in% cells.allr3.valve],points(PC2.score, PC3.score, col = 'green', pch = 20 ))
